---
import Default from '../layouts/Default.astro';
---
<Default title="Harshith Kantamneni">

  <section class="hero">
    <div class="hero-parallax-layer hero-parallax-layer-1" aria-hidden="true"></div>
    <div class="hero-parallax-layer hero-parallax-layer-2" aria-hidden="true"></div>
    <div class="container">
      <span class="index-number">001 / Thesis</span>
      <h1>I design and run autonomous AI labs.</h1>
      <p class="lede">
        Each one is a persistent organization of specialist agents that ships
        engineering and research work over long horizons. This site is the public
        surface for their methodology, system reports, and operating decisions.
      </p>
      <div class="hero-meta">
        <span>Active development</span>
        <span>Methodology published</span>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="reveal">
    <div class="container">
      <div style="display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 2fr; gap: var(--space-8); align-items: start; max-width: 80rem; margin: 0 auto;">
        <div><span class="section-marker">002 / Background</span></div>
        <div>
          <p style="font-size: var(--fs-body-lg); line-height: 1.5; max-width: 48rem;">
            GPU systems engineer with a background in CUDA kernel optimization,
            memory hierarchy reverse engineering, and ML-driven systems work. I build
            autonomous AI labs as a parallel research effort, applying performance
            engineering discipline to the operations of multi-agent systems.
          </p>
          <p style="color: var(--text-secondary);"><a href="/about">Read more →</a></p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section style="border-top: 1px solid var(--border-hairline);" class="reveal">
    <div class="container">
      <span class="section-marker">003 / Labs</span>
      <h2 style="max-width: 24ch;">Each lab is a persistent organization that plans, executes, evaluates, and self-corrects over long horizons.</h2>

      <div class="card-grid">
        <a href="/labs/hive" class="tilt-card">
          <div class="card-inner">
            <span class="status-pill live">Live</span>
            <h3>HIVE Product Lab</h3>
            <p class="meta">Product engineering · active since 2026</p>
            <p>
              Specialist agents for architecture, mobile engineering, code review,
              red team, evaluator, and knowledge management. CI-bound external verdict
              and pre-registered streak falsifiers.
            </p>
            <div class="stack">
              <span>Rust</span><span>Mobile FFI</span><span>Cross-platform</span>
            </div>
          </div>
        </a>

        <a href="/labs/autonomous-research" class="tilt-card">
          <div class="card-inner">
            <span class="status-pill live">Live</span>
            <h3>Autonomous Research Lab</h3>
            <p class="meta">Research operations · long-horizon experimentation</p>
            <p>
              Tiered persistent memory, pre-registration discipline, governance ledgers,
              reproducibility gates, honest negative results. Small-model experimentation
              under constrained local compute.
            </p>
            <div class="stack">
              <span>Small models</span><span>Pre-registration</span><span>Tiered memory</span>
            </div>
          </div>
        </a>
      </div>

      <p style="margin-top: var(--space-6);"><a href="/labs">All labs →</a></p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section style="border-top: 1px solid var(--border-hairline);" class="reveal">
    <div class="container">
      <span class="section-marker">004 / Latest report</span>
      <div style="max-width: 60rem;">
        <a href="/reports/recursive-verification-surface-collapse" class="tilt-card" style="display: block;">
          <div class="card-inner">
            <p class="meta" style="margin: 0 0 var(--space-3);">May 15, 2026 · 3,200 words · 14 min read</p>
            <h3 style="font-size: 2rem; margin-bottom: var(--space-4);">
              Recursive Verification-Surface Collapse in Self-Graded Autonomous Engineering Systems
            </h3>
            <p style="font-size: var(--fs-body-lg); color: var(--text-secondary); max-width: 50rem; margin: 0;">
              Three times in 100 cycles, my autonomous lab passed its own tests while quietly
              breaking. Each break was at a deeper layer than the last. Notes on the null-set
              principal problem and three structural principles for disrupting it.
            </p>
            <p style="margin-top: var(--space-5); margin-bottom: 0;">
              <span style="font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: var(--fs-small); color: var(--accent);">Read report →</span>
            </p>
          </div>
        </a>
      </div>
      <p style="margin-top: var(--space-7);"><a href="/reports">All reports →</a></p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section style="border-top: 1px solid var(--border-hairline);" class="reveal">
    <div class="container-medium">
      <span class="section-marker">005 / Recent notes</span>
      <h2 style="font-size: var(--fs-h3);">Lab observations and quick takes.</h2>
      <ul class="writing-list">
        <li>
          <span class="date">May 5</span>
          <a href="/notes/byte-identical-builds" class="title">Twelve cycles of byte-identical builds</a>
          <span class="length">~330w</span>
        </li>
        <li>
          <span class="date">May 3</span>
          <a href="/notes/tier-per-task" class="title">Tier dispatchers per task, not per role</a>
          <span class="length">~310w</span>
        </li>
        <li>
          <span class="date">May 2</span>
          <a href="/notes/llm-judge-bias" class="title">Same-family LLM judge bias is real</a>
          <span class="length">~290w</span>
        </li>
      </ul>
      <p style="margin-top: var(--space-5);"><a href="/notes">All notes →</a></p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section style="border-top: 1px solid var(--border-hairline);" class="reveal">
    <div class="container">
      <span class="section-marker">006 / Work</span>
      <h2 style="max-width: 24ch;">Selected projects from years of GPU performance and systems work.</h2>
      <div class="card-grid">
        <article class="card">
          <p class="meta">2026 · Public</p>
          <h3 style="font-size: 1.5rem;">Triton vs cuBLAS Benchmarks</h3>
          <p>
            CUDA and Triton kernels for LLM-shaped GEMM and fused linear ops. Measured
            p50 latency, throughput, bandwidth, and jitter on NVIDIA GPUs.
          </p>
          <div class="stack"><span>C++</span><span>CUDA</span><span>Triton</span></div>
        </article>
        <article class="card">
          <p class="meta">In progress</p>
          <h3 style="font-size: 1.5rem;">MI300X Memory Reverse Engineering</h3>
          <p>
            CUDA microbenchmarks measuring L2, L3, and HBM latency and bandwidth.
            Calibrating a gem5 MI300X memory subsystem to reduce HW vs sim mismatch.
          </p>
          <div class="stack"><span>CUDA</span><span>gem5</span></div>
        </article>
        <article class="card">
          <p class="meta">2025 · Public</p>
          <h3 style="font-size: 1.5rem;">Edge LLM GPU Profiling</h3>
          <p>
            Performance profiling on NVIDIA Jetson Orin Nano. Analyzed LLM attention
            and KV-cache decode workloads with Nsight Systems and FlashAttention.
          </p>
          <div class="stack"><span>Jetson</span><span>Nsight</span></div>
        </article>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section id="subscribe" style="border-top: 1px solid var(--border-hairline); background: var(--bg-surface);" class="reveal">
    <div class="container-medium">
      <span class="section-marker">007 / Subscribe</span>
      <h2 style="font-size: var(--fs-h3); max-width: 22ch; margin-top: 0;">One email per month, around 5 minute read.</h2>
      <p style="font-size: var(--fs-body-lg); color: var(--text-secondary); max-width: 38rem;">
        Curated digest of the month's reports, notable observations from running the labs,
        and anything I think you would find useful. No spam, unsubscribe anytime.
      </p>
      <form action="https://buttondown.com/api/emails/embed-subscribe/harshith" method="post" target="popupwindow" class="newsletter-form">
        <input type="email" name="email" placeholder="you@example.com" required>
        <button type="submit">Subscribe</button>
      </form>
    </div>
  </section>

</Default>
